data.title: MLC_ELGs: Machine Learning Classifiers for intermediate redshift Emission Line Galaxies
data.name: MLC_ELGs
data.description: Machine Learning Classifiers for intermediate redshift Emission Line Galaxies

evidence: "In this work, we address this problem using four supervised machine learning classification algorithms... Our publicly available code and trained models will be instrumental for classifying emission line galaxies in upcoming wide-field spectroscopic surveys."

"### scikit_kfold_training.py
The code for training the model... Run the code as: python3 scikit_kfold_training.py 'rf'."

"### scikit_kfold_classifier.py
Use a trained model to make classifications to 0.32<z<0.8 emission line galaxies."
